3
00:00:12.181 --> 00:00:17.860
the King Kong of musical form, whatever
you want to call it, sonata allegro form.

4
00:00:17.860 --> 00:00:19.230
Why is it so important?

5
00:00:19.230 --> 00:00:23.180
Well because it's the most
frequently used of the classical and

6
00:00:23.180 --> 00:00:29.100
romantic era forms and it opens most
multi-movement classical genres.

7
00:00:29.100 --> 00:00:35.440
It's the form that begins a symphony,
a string quartet, a concerto or a sonata.

8
00:00:35.440 --> 00:00:40.630
Indeed we get our term sonata
allegro form from the sonata.

9
00:00:40.630 --> 00:00:43.920
Let's go back to the slide of
the concerto and the sonata.

10
00:00:45.240 --> 00:00:48.550
Sonatas begin with
movements that are fast.

11
00:00:48.550 --> 00:00:54.410
So the term sonata-allegro
is taken from this process.

12
00:00:54.410 --> 00:00:57.280
First movements in sonatas went this way.

13
00:00:57.280 --> 00:01:00.360
They were fast and
they went according to this form, so

14
00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:02.250
we call it sonata-allegro form.

15
00:01:02.250 --> 00:01:09.080
